songs.title: Rust Belt Renegade
songs.description: Rust Belt Renegade tells the story of a small-town mechanic, tired of corporate greed and environmental destruction swallowing his community.  He channels his anger and frustration into a fightback, leading a grassroots rebellion against a polluting mega-corporation. The song charts his journey from quiet desperation to defiant leadership, culminating in a hard-won victory and a sense of empowerment for the forgotten people.
songs.lyrics:
(Intro - driving electric guitar riff with banjo accents)

(Verse 1)
Cracked asphalt, choked with dust,
Factory smoke, a bitter gust.
Another promise, broken vow,
This town's bleeding, I don't know how.
They took the river, stole the land,
Left us hollow, a broken band.
But the fire's burning, deep inside,
Gonna fight this battle, side by side.

(Chorus)
Rust Belt Renegade, I'm raising up my hand,
Fighting for the future, taking back the land.
No more empty promises, no more silent pleas,
We're the forgotten voices, carried on the breeze.
Rust Belt Renegade, we're breaking through the chains,
Washing clean the damage, healing all the pains.

(Verse 2)
They built their empire on our sweat,
Ignoring warnings, haven't paid their debt.
But we're organizing, standing tall,
Answering the call, before we fall.
From the mines to the mills we stand,
Taking back our home, our sacred land.
With wrench and hammer, we'll reclaim,
What they stole, in their greedy game.

(Chorus)
Rust Belt Renegade, I'm raising up my hand,
Fighting for the future, taking back the land.
No more empty promises, no more silent pleas,
We're the forgotten voices, carried on the breeze.
Rust Belt Renegade, we're breaking through the chains,
Washing clean the damage, healing all the pains.

(Bridge)
They underestimated our strength and might,
Their corporate greed met the firelight.
We're rising from the ashes, strong and true,
Building a better future, me and you.

(Chorus)
Rust Belt Renegade, I'm raising up my hand,
Fighting for the future, taking back the land.
No more empty promises, no more silent pleas,
We're the forgotten voices, carried on the breeze.
Rust Belt Renegade, we're breaking through the chains,
Washing clean the damage, healing all the pains.

(Outro - extended guitar solo fading into banjo and hand claps)
songs.soundsLike: Driving electric guitar riffs with a strong country rock feel.  Banjo and acoustic guitar provide a rootsy counterpoint.  Drums are powerful and driving, providing a solid backbone. Bass is prominent and punchy. Vocals are strong and slightly gravelly, conveying both anger and determination. Production is clean and crisp, with a slight emphasis on the raw energy of the instruments.
songs.singers: Powerful, gritty vocals with a slight rasp, capable of conveying both vulnerability and defiant strength.

songs.title: Flesh on Flesh
songs.description:
Here's a two-sentence description and a one-sentence "sounds like" for the song:

This is a raw, high-energy country tune about a night fueled by pure, unbridled lust and primal connection. It's a vivid snapshot of intense physical desire, leaving nothing but a lingering heat and the ghost of a wicked touch.

Sounds like Johnny Cash's rebellious spirit got tangled up with Chris Stapleton's soulful grit, then spent a wild night with Tyler Childers' storytelling prowess.
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Sunrise paints the world in grey, another damn day begins
Same old grind, same old pain, the weight of all my sins
But last night, the moon hung low, a different kind of fire
It scorched the damn shadows out, fueled every dark desire

(Chorus)
Flesh on flesh, whiskey sighs, tangled in the sheets
Fire in these bones still glowin', a pulse in my bare feet
Steam from the shower, hazy air, a hunger wild and free
Her wicked touch, holding tight, that's what she burned in me.

(Verse 2)
Shes a wildfire in the hollow, a hurricane on the breeze
She melted the ice that bound my soul, brought me to my knees
From separate rooms, to tangled limbs, a craving took its hold
Her whispers were a flash flood, more precious than pure gold.

(Chorus)
Flesh on flesh, whiskey sighs, tangled in the sheets
Fire in these bones still glowin', a pulse in my bare feet
Steam from the shower, hazy air, a hunger wild and free
Her wicked touch, holding tight, that's what she burned in me.

(Bridge)
Never thought I'd find a moment like this, a spark to scorch the grey
A taste of pure lightning, hot and strong, that's gonna light my way
The work may call, the road may wait, but I'll remember this tonight
A memory to hold me close, beneath that blinding light.

(Chorus)
Flesh on flesh, whiskey sighs, tangled in the sheets
Fire in these bones still glowin', a pulse in my bare feet
Steam from the shower, hazy air, a hunger wild and free
Her wicked touch, holding tight, that's what she burned in me.
songs.soundsLike:
This is a raw, high-energy country tune about a night fueled by pure, unbridled lust and primal connection. It's a vivid snapshot of intense physical desire, leaving nothing but a lingering heat and the ghost of a wicked touch.

Sounds like driving acoustic guitar and a wailing fiddle underpin a gritty, gravel-throated vocal delivering urgent, untamed tales with subtle bluegrass undertones.

songs.title: Kiss me slow (or don't)
songs.description: A high-energy country tune reminiscent of Johnny Cash's rebellious spirit mixed with the soulful grit of Chris Stapleton and the storytelling prowess of Tyler Childers.  The song depicts a passionate, whirlwind night with a woman, told through vivid metaphors and imagery reflecting the raw energy of Alex Wilson's life. The lyrics use the contrast between the harshness of his daily existence (coal mining) and the unexpected tenderness of this encounter to create a compelling narrative. The instrumentation features prominent acoustic guitar and fiddle, creating a driving rhythm that reflects the urgency and intensity of the nights events, with subtle bluegrass undertones.
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Sunrise paints the mountain grey, another day begins
Same old grind, same old pain, same coal dust on my skin
But last night, the moon hung low, a different kind of light
Burned away the shadows deep, and chased away the night

(Chorus)
Coal dust kisses, whiskey sighs, tangled in the sheets
Fire in the ashes glowin', a rhythm to our feet
Steam from the shower, hazy air, a love both wild and free
Coal dust kisses, holdin' tight, that's what she meant to me.

(Verse 2)
Shes a fire in the hollow, a whisper in the breeze
She melts the ice that binds my soul, puts my heart at ease
From separate rooms, to tangled limbs, a story takes its hold
Her laughters like a mountain stream, more precious than pure gold.

(Chorus)
Coal dust kisses, whiskey sighs, tangled in the sheets
Fire in the ashes glowin', a rhythm to our feet
Steam from the shower, hazy air, a love both wild and free
Coal dust kisses, holdin' tight, that's what she meant to me.

(Bridge)
Never thought I'd find a moment like this, a spark to chase the grey
A taste of sunshine, sweet and strong, that's gonna light my way
The mine may call, the work may wait, but I'll remember this tonight
A memory to hold me close, beneath the mountain light.

(Chorus)
Coal dust kisses, whiskey sighs, tangled in the sheets
Fire in the ashes glowin', a rhythm to our feet
Steam from the shower, hazy air, a love both wild and free
Coal dust kisses, holdin' tight, that's what she meant to me.
songs.soundsLike: Raspy, powerful vocals with a slight twang. Driving rhythm section with prominent acoustic guitar and fiddle, creating a fast-paced, upbeat feel.  The instrumentation is largely acoustic, with a focus on strong melodic lines and a percussive feel from the instrumental work.
songs.singers: A vocalist with a similar rasp and vocal power to Chris Stapleton or Jamey Johnson would suit this song well.

songs.title: Champagne and Sin
songs.description: This song tells the story of Alex Wilson, a young coal miner with a hidden talent for songwriting, unexpectedly caught up in a wild bachelorette party.  The lyrics blend his rough-around-the-edges Appalachian upbringing with the chaotic energy of a night gone wrong, creating a unique blend of outlaw country reminiscent of Waylon Jennings' rebellious spirit and the heartfelt storytelling of Chris Stapleton. The fiddle and acoustic guitar provide a raw, authentic backdrop, echoing the simplicity and intensity of his life.  The song's narrative arc reflects the contrast between his quiet, introspective nature and the unrestrained celebration, showcasing a surprising vulnerability while maintaining the grit and honesty that define his persona.  The energetic tempo and driving rhythm, punctuated by moments of quiet reflection, build a narrative that reflects the surprising depth hidden beneath the surface.
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1:
Six-foot-two and coal dust stained,
Never thought Id see a bride this tamed.
Came for a fix, a bottle of moonshine,
Ended up in a bachelorette party, a scene so fine.
Fiddle started screamin', a bluegrass breakdown,
These city girls ain't afraid to let their hair down.

Chorus:
Coal dust and champagne, a wild, wild night,
Diamonds and dirt, bathed in neon light.
Never seen nothin' like it, a whirlwind of sound,
Lost in the chaos, never touched the ground.

Verse 2:
Whiskey flowed like the Cumberland's stream,
Their laughter echoed, a whiskey-soaked dream.
One girl's eyes held mine, a spark in the haze,
Saw somethin' in me, beyond these coal-stained days.

Chorus:
Coal dust and champagne, a wild, wild night,
Diamonds and dirt, bathed in neon light.
Never seen nothin' like it, a whirlwind of sound,
Lost in the chaos, never touched the ground.

Bridge:
Sunrise crept in, the party's gone slow,
Left with the memories, a bittersweet glow.
Empty bottles and whispers of truth,
A glimpse of a life beyond my youth.

Chorus:
Coal dust and champagne, a wild, wild night,
Diamonds and dirt, bathed in neon light.
Never seen nothin' like it, a whirlwind of sound,
Lost in the chaos, never touched the ground.
songs.soundsLike: Raspy, powerful vocals with a slight twang. Driving acoustic guitar rhythm, prominent fiddle melodies, strong percussion that maintains energy without overwhelming the instrumentation.  The production is raw and unpolished, keeping the focus on the instrumentation and vocal delivery.
songs.singers: A vocalist with a raspy, powerful voice similar to Chris Stapleton or Tyler Childers would be ideal.

songs.title: Coal Dust & Whiskey
songs.description: This song tells the story of Alex Wilson, a young coal miner, grappling with the harsh realities of his life.  He pours his experiences into a blend of country and hip-hop, reflecting influences like Johnny Cash's gritty honesty, Waylon Jennings' outlaw spirit, and the soulful power of Chris Stapleton and Tyler Childers. The lyrics detail a typical Friday night  getting drunk to numb the pain, only to wake up and face the grueling work in the coal mine the next morning.  The hip-hop influence adds a contemporary edge to the classic country storytelling, creating a unique sound that's both raw and relatable. It's a song about resilience, the struggle to survive, and the quiet dignity of a hardworking man.
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1:
Sun dips low, another shift is done,
Another day of dust beneath the sun.
Head's a-throbbin', body's beat up, sore,
But tonight, forget the pain, I'll want some more.
Whiskey's callin', a siren in the night,
Drownin' sorrows in that amber light.

Chorus:
Coal dust and whiskey, that's my Friday night,
Washin' away the darkness, holdin' on tight.
Wake up early, sun ain't even peekin',
But the coal mine's waitin', my soul's still bleakin'.

Verse 2:
Empty bottle, empty promises I made,
To myself, to a life I could've swayed.
But this town's a grip, a hand upon my throat,
Workin' hard, but still ain't got a boat.
To sail away from this life of grime and sweat,
Another Friday's coming, ain't forgot it yet.

Chorus:
Coal dust and whiskey, that's my Friday night,
Washin' away the darkness, holdin' on tight.
Wake up early, sun ain't even peekin',
But the coal mine's waitin', my soul's still bleakin'.

Bridge:
Fiddle solo - mournful, yet defiant, mirroring the internal struggle.
(Beat switches to a more stripped-down, acoustic feel, resembling a Tyler Childers ballad)
My mama's ghost whispers in the coal dust haze,
Says, "Boy, find a way to escape these days."
But the mountain's shadow's long, it wraps me tight,
And the rhythm of the hammer keeps me in the fight.

Chorus:
Coal dust and whiskey, that's my Friday night,
Washin' away the darkness, holdin' on tight.
Wake up early, sun ain't even peekin',
But the coal mine's waitin', my soul's still bleakin'.

Outro:
(Music fades out with a final, lingering fiddle note and a repeated, low acoustic guitar strum)
Coal dust... whiskey...
songs.soundsLike: Energetic hip-hop track featuring syncopated, percussive beats as its backbone. Raspy vocals cut through layers of soulful acoustic guitar and swelling fiddle melodies. The dynamic arrangement balances raw energy with undertones of sadness, letting fiddle lines deepen the emotional texture.

songs.title: Tailgate Fire
songs.description: A high-energy country song about an unexpected and passionate encounter at a tailgate party, told from the perspective of a young, hard-working coal miner who is usually reserved and avoids social interaction.
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1:
(Acoustic guitar intro - fingerpicked, reminiscent of early Johnny Cash)
Fiddle joins in, a driving beat
Dust on my boots, another long shift beat
Tailgate party, smellin' of beer and coal
Never thought I'd be here, losin' all control
Just came for the whiskey, to drown out the day
Didn't expect her laugh, or the way she would sway

Chorus:
(Tempo picks up, fiddle becomes more prominent, drums kick in)
Tailgate fire burnin' bright, under the Kentucky night
Sparks flyin' higher than the pines, mixed with whiskey and sweet wine
Didn't plan on this feelin', this rush, this surprise
But that girl, she set my heart ablaze

Verse 2:
Fiddle plays a bluesy riff
Her eyes, like the sky, clear, vast, and bright
Talkin' 'bout nothin', but feelin' somethin' right
Workin' hands, calloused and strong
She held mine tight, all night long
Coal dust on my shirt, sweat on her brow
Didn't know heaven could feel like this somehow

Chorus:
Tailgate fire burnin' bright, under the Kentucky night
Sparks flyin' higher than the pines, mixed with whiskey and sweet wine
Didn't plan on this feelin', this rush, this surprise
But that girl, she set my heart ablaze

Bridge:
(Tempo slows slightly, more emphasis on acoustic guitar and vocals - Chris Stapleton influence)
Used to the silence, the shadows, the pain
But her touch broke through, washed away the rain
Never thought I'd find solace in a drunken haze
But she showed me a kindness, in a thousand different ways

Chorus:
Tailgate fire burnin' bright, under the Kentucky night
Sparks flyin' higher than the pines, mixed with whiskey and sweet wine
Didn't plan on this feelin', this rush, this surprise
But that girl, she set my heart ablaze
(Fiddle and guitar outro - fades out)
songs.soundsLike: Driving beat with prominent fiddle and acoustic guitar.  Strong, slightly raspy vocals, transitioning from a reserved tone in verses to more powerful delivery in the chorus.  The chorus features a full drum kit, adding energy and intensity to the track.  The bridge features a slower tempo with a focus on the acoustic guitar and vocals, creating a more intimate and reflective mood.  The instrumentation includes acoustic and electric guitars, fiddle, drums, and possibly bass.
songs.singers: Alex Wilson's voice should be raw and emotive, similar to Chris Stapleton or a younger Johnny Cash.  The delivery should be honest and unaffected.

songs.title: Iron in My Soul
songs.description: A powerful and uplifting anthem about resilience and overcoming adversity. 'Iron in My Soul' tells the story of a woman who has faced hardship and emerged stronger, her spirit forged in the fires of experience.  The song blends elements of country, rock, and folk, creating a rich and dynamic soundscape that reflects the emotional depth of the lyrics.  It's a song about finding strength in vulnerability, celebrating survival, and embracing the scars that tell a story of triumph.
songs.lyrics:
**Verse 1**  
Kicked up dust on a road of shattered dreams,  
Wore my heart in patches, frayed at the seams.  
Fell hard in the shadows, where the cold winds howl,  
But I clawed my way up, aint stayin down now.  

**Chorus**  
Got iron in my soul, forged in fire and pain,  
Every scars a story, every tears a flame.  
Im standin tall, unbroken, with a heart thats bold,  
Singin loud, Im alive, with iron in my soul!  

**Verse 2**  
Barroom nights taught me how to fight,  
Whiskey truths burned under neon light.  
Lost love, found grace in a jukeboxs hum,  
Each notes a spark for the woman Ive become.  

**Chorus**  
Got iron in my soul, forged in fire and pain,  
Every scars a story, every tears a flame.  
Im standin tall, unbroken, with a heart thats bold,  
Singin loud, Im alive, with iron in my soul!  

**Bridge**  
They tried to bend me, tried to break my stride,  
But my roots run deeper than their whispered lies.  
With a voice like thunder, Ill shake the ground,  
This iron hearts the sweetest sound!  

**Chorus**  
Got iron in my soul, forged in fire and pain,  
Every scars a story, every tears a flame.  
Im standin tall, unbroken, with a heart thats bold,  
Singin loud, Im alive, with iron in my soul!  

**Outro**  
(Claps, guitar swell)  
Iron in my soul, itll never rust away,  
Carved my name in the stars, here to stay.
songs.soundsLike: A blend of twangy electric and rich acoustic guitars drives the anthem, tight with full band energy, pounding drums, and soulful fiddle lines weaving throughout, Warm organ pads fill out the mix, Powerful female vocals with reverb and layered harmonies create a dynamic, crowd-energizing hook
songs.singers: Alex Wilson (lead vocals), with backing vocals by  (Suggestion:  a trio of female vocalists for richer harmonies)

songs.title: Fistfights and Firelight
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Bottle smashed loud, barroom turned to hell,
Knuckles flew fast neath a neon spell.
Whiskey burned hot, boots scuffed the floor,
Dodged a right hook, then I saw you by the door.
Chorus
Fistfights and firelight, hearts runnin wild,
Chaos and your eyes cut through like a child.
From a busted-up night to a spark that wont fade,
Darlin, our love was a barroom crusade.
Verse 2
Jukebox wailed a lonesome rebel tune,
Blood on my lip, but I caught your moon.
You tossed me a grin, like a dare wrapped in lace,
Stole my fightin soul with that angels face.
Chorus
Fistfights and firelight, hearts runnin wild,
Chaos and your eyes cut through like a child.
From a busted-up night to a spark that wont fade,
Darlin, our love was a barroom crusade.
Bridge
Broken chairs and whiskey stains,
Outlaw hearts dont feel no chains.
Through the smoke and the sin, we carved our own way,
Turned a brawl into forever that day.
Chorus
Fistfights and firelight, hearts runnin wild,
Chaos and your eyes cut through like a child.
From a busted-up night to a spark that wont fade,
Darlin, our love was a barroom crusade.
Outro
Now we dance slow where the jukebox hums,
From fistfights to firelight, our battles won.
songs.soundsLike: A twangy electric guitar and robust acoustic lead a full band with pounding drums, a growling bass, and fiery fiddle riffs, crafting a polished, outlaw country anthem, raspy vocals carry reverb, with gritty harmonies in the chorus, delivering a rowdy, radio-ready sound

songs.title: Drinkin to Remember
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Tennessees callin with a whiskey shot,
Jack burns smooth, hits the perfect spot.
Georgias got moonshine, jar lit by the stars,
Raise it high, were roarin in the bars!

Chorus
Drinkin to remember, raise em to the sky!
Toastin every memory, never say goodbye!
From state to state, were chasin that glow,
Drinkin to remember, let the good times flow!

Verse 2
Alabamas slingin cold beers by the case,
Bud Light fizz, puts a grin on my face.
Kentucky bourbon, like a warm ol friend,
Sips tellin stories that never end.

Chorus
Drinkin to remember, raise em to the sky!
Toastin every memory, never say goodbye!
From state to state, were chasin that glow,
Drinkin to remember, let the good times flow!

Verse 3
Texas tequila, with a lime and a sting,
Shots in the sun, make the whole crowd sing.
Mississippis got rum, sweet as cane in the breeze,
Partys just startin, were dancin with ease!

Haulin dreams with a heavy load.

Singin through storms where my hope nearly died.

Chased a light down a barroom haze,
Lost my heart in a thousand ways.
Scars tell tales of the fights Ive braved,
But my voice still roars where the souls been saved.

Chorus (Both)
Worn out wings, still flyin high,
Carryin dreams neath a broken sky.
Through the hurt, were holdin on tight,
Worn out wings, soarin through the night!

Verse 3 (Alex)
Your songs a river, cool on my pain,
Pulls me from shadows, breaks every chain.
That fire in your eyes, like a beacons call,
Lifts my battered heart when Im bound to fall.

Verse 4 (Ashley)
Your truth cuts deep, like a whiskeys burn,
Steadies my soul when the tides all turn.

Worn out wings, still flyin high,
Carryin dreams neath a broken sky.
Through the hurt, were holdin on tight,
Worn out wings, soarin through the night!

Worn out wings fueled by stubborn love!

Worn out wings, still flyin high,
Carryin dreams neath a broken sky.
Through the hurt, were holdin on tight,
Worn out wings, soarin through the night!

Worn out wings, well never fall,
Two tough hearts answerin the call.

songs.title: Mountain's Heavy Hand
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1) The timbers cracked like a sinner's bones
Eight hundred feet of Kentucky stone
Heard the mountain groan and give a sigh
And seal us off from a patch of sky
Old Man Miller, he started to pray
Asked for 'Grace' to light the way
Well, this old guitar's all I got to give
So hush now, brothers while we live.

(Chorus) This aint no church, no steeple grand
Just coal-black dust on a tremblin hand
But well find a hymn beneath the seam
In the diesel smoke and the dyin beam
Let the mountain have its heavy say
Well sing it down till the light of day
Yall just breathe in slow, and understand
We're holdin' on 'gainst the mountain's heavy hand.

(Verse 2) I see your faces, etched in fear
Taste the iron in the thinnin' air
Reminds me of a different kind of dark
A different rage that left its mark
But down here, boys, were all the same
Just souls callin' out a different name
From a place that taught us how to bleed
And plant our hope like a mustard seed.

(Chorus) 'Cause this aint no church, no steeple grand
Just coal-black dust on a tremblin hand
But well find a hymn beneath the seam
In the diesel smoke and the dyin beam
Let the mountain have its heavy say
Well sing it down till the light of day
Yall just breathe in slow, and understand
We're holdin' on 'gainst the mountain's heavy hand.

(Bridge) Lord, if you're listenin' through the rock and the slate
I ain't askin' you to change our fate
Just let this worn-out six-string ring
And give these tired lungs one more song to sing
A broken chord, a sinner's grace
For every shadow in this place

(Outro) The mountain's heavy hand
Just breathe it in breathe it low
Breathe it out let the darkness know
were still here.
songs.soundsLike: The song opens with slow, resonant 4/4 time; delicate fingerpicked guitar, understated bass, and soft percussion create an intimate verse texture, The chorus erupts with forceful strummed guitar, bold drums, deep swelling bass, and warm atmospheric pads, amplifying a somber yet defiant mood

songs.title: Moonshine and Church Bells
songs.lyrics:
The jar gets passed 'round a hickory fire,
Singin' off-key with a backwoods choir.
That white lightnin' hits you, clears out the doubt,
Makes a fella feel what the preachin's all about.
We're hollerin' stories the pines have all heard,
Slurrin' every syllable of every other word,
And the moon hangs above us like a holy host,
Givin' its blessin' to the sinners who drink the most.

Then the sun comes crawlin' up the eastern ridge,
My head's still poundin' on a rickety bridge.
Got the taste of charcoal still stuck on my tongue,
Feel a hundred years older than when the night was young.
That's when I hear it, from the valley down below,
A sound that's meant to save you, but it rings so slow
First Baptist sendin' out its Sunday sound,
While we're still tryin' to bury the evidence in the ground.

It's moonshine and church bells, a holy kind of beat,
One saves your soul, the other saves your feet from the cold.
It's Saturday's fire and Sunday's golden rule,
Makin' a good-timin', hymn-singin', Appalachian fool.
Lord have mercy, I know just where I stand
With a foot in the creek bed and one in the promised land.

I see ol' man Hemphill, who bought a quart last night,
Hidin' in the back pew, lookin' for the light.
His wife is fannin' furious, singin' *Rock of Ages*,
While he's sweatin' out the devil from last night's rages.
The preacher's talkin' brimstone, talkin' 'bout the fall,
And I reckon half the congregation can't remember it at all,
'Cause we were all there howlin', united in our sin,
Now we're all here prayin' they might just let us in.

I ain't makin' fun, I'm just tellin' what is true,
The good Lord made the corn grow, and the yeast to help it through.
He made the fiddle scream and the organ whisper low,
Maybe one's for gettin' ready and the other's for the show.
Its a complicated rhythm for a simple man.

It's moonshine and church bells, a holy kind of beat,
One saves your soul, the other saves your feet from the cold.
It's Saturday's fire and Sunday's golden rule,
Makin' a good-timin', hymn-singin', Appalachian fool.
Lord have mercy, I know just where I stand
With a foot in the creek bed and one in the promised land.

Yeah, the promised land...
Ringing in my ears now...
Don't know which is which.
songs.soundsLike: A relentless rush of Appalachian bluegrass energy, propelled by driving acoustic guitar and punchy upright bass, Banjo fires rapid syncopations, fiddle lets loose with high, piercing leads, while tightly punctuated mandolin chords add punch, Gritty baritone vocals cut through confidently. Real crossover potential due to the near rap-like verses.

songs.title: Runnin Late to Church
songs.description:
Performance Details

Sound Description (Acoustic): Bright acoustic guitar strums with a cheeky banjo riff, gravelly vocals delivering a foot-tapping, gospel-tinged romp, claps adding barroom charm.

Sound Description (Recording): Polished country-rock, jangly guitars, lively fiddle, and driving drums, with group harmonies on the chorus for a radio-ready, singalong vibe.
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Woke up with a stranger, tangled in the sheets,
Lipstick on my collar, boots stillMayors weight on my feet.
Clocks tickin past nine, preachers gonna frown,
Got a potluck dish to save my soul in this town.

Chorus
Runnin late to church, with a sinners grin,
Last nights whiskey still burnin deep within.
Tater casseroles ridin shotgun in my truck,
Prayin for grace, hopin for luck.

Verse 2
Her perfumes on my shirt, cant shake the devils sway,
Dashboard Jesus judgin every mile I stray.
Gravy flies, Im speedin down that old dirt road,
Gotta get to service fore the choir sings.

Chorus
Runnin late to church, with a sinners grin,
Last nights whiskey still burnin deep within.
Tater casseroles ridin shotgun in my truck,
Prayin for grace, hopin for luck.

Bridge
Barstool confessions wont cleanse my soul,
But a pan of cornbread might make the preacher whole.
Slide in the back pew, dodge the deacons stare,
Lord, forgive me, Im almost there.

Chorus
Runnin late to church, with a sinners grin,
Last nights whiskey still burnin deep within.
Tater casseroles ridin shotgun in my truck,
Prayin for grace, hopin for luck.

Outro
(Claps, hollers, banjo twang)
Late to church, but Im here with my dish,
Saved by the potluck, thank God for this wish!

songs.title: Sound of Silence
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
One AM, bar closed down
Took a shot of whiskey, it ain't helpin' now
To shut my mind off, stop it from racin'
I turn to what I've been chasin'

[Chorus]
The sound of silence
I find it on the road at night drivin'
In my bed when the storm is outside it
It's like a choir singin' to my soul
I've been prayin' that I'll find it
In my head, so I can't deny it
When I do, you know I'll invite it
Into my heart and never let it go
It's the sound of silence

[Verse 2]
'Fore you know it, your life is half gone
Still tryin' to figure out where you belong
To shut my mind off, stop it from racin'
I turn to what I've been chasin'

[Chorus]
The sound of silence
I find it on the road at night drivin'
In my bed when the storm is outside it
It's like a choir singin' to my soul
I've been prayin' that I'll find it
In my head, so I can't deny it
When I do, you know I'll invite it
Into my heart and never let it go
It's the sound of silence

[Verse 3]
Everywhere I go, everywhere I go
It never seems to leave me alone
Everywhere I go, everywhere I go
I'm drownin' in this world

[Chorus]
And I need the sound of silence
I find it on the road at night drivin'
In my bed when the storm is outside it
It's like a choir singin' to my soul
I've been prayin' that I'll find it
In my head, so I can't deny it
When I do, you know I'll invite it
Into my heart and never let it go
It's the sound of silence
songs.soundsLike: A traditional country ballad reminiscent of George Jones and Merle Haggard, "Sound of Silence" features mournful steel guitar and heartfelt vocals telling a story of quiet desperation.  Alex Wilson's delivery is raw and authentic, showcasing classic country instrumentation and a contemplative mood over a traditional production style.

To shut my mind off, stop it from racin'
I turn to what I've been chasin'

[Chorus]
The sound of silence
I find it on the road at night drivin'
In my bed when the storm is outside it
It's like a choir singin' to my soul

In my head, so I can't deny it
When I do, you know I'll invite it
Into my heart and never let it go
It's the sound of silence

[Verse 2]
'Fore you know it, your life is half gone
Still tryin' to figure out where you belong
To shut my mind off, stop it from racin'
I turn to what I've been chasin'

[Chorus]
The sound of silence
I find it on the road at night drivin'
In my bed when the storm is outside it

When I do, you know I'll invite it
Into my heart and never let it go
It's the sound of silence

Everywhere I go, everywhere I go
It never seems to leave me alone
Everywhere I go, everywhere I go
I'm drownin' in this world

[Chorus]
And I need the sound of silence
I find it on the road at night drivin'
In my bed when the storm is outside it
It's like a choir singin' to my soul
I've been prayin' that I'll find it
In my head, so I can't deny it
When I do, you know I'll invite it
Into my heart and never let it go
It's the sound of silence

### Sounds Like
A traditional country ballad reminiscent of George Jones and Merle Haggard, "Sound of Silence" features mournful steel guitar and heartfelt vocals telling a story of quiet desperation.  Alex Wilson's delivery is raw and authentic, showcasing classic country instrumentation and a contemplative mood over a traditional production style.

songs.title: Taco Town
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Rolled into town with a hunger to tame,
Saw a food truck sign, didnt know the name.
Taaah-cooows, I drawled, with a puzzled grin,
Somethin new was callin, let the feast begin!

Chorus
Its taco time, yall, grab a messy bite!
Corn and meat, so cheap, lightin up the night!
Spicy kick, hands slick, lovin every thrill,
Taco time, givin my heart a fill!

Verse 2
Bit that tortilla, flavors burstin free,
Juice down my chin, felt like heaven to me.
Onions, cilantro, a little hot sting,
This workin mans food makes my soul wanna sing.

Chorus
Its taco time, yall, grab a messy bite!
Corn and meat, so cheap, lightin up the night!
Spicy kick, hands slick, lovin every thrill,
Taco time, givin my heart a fill!

Bridge
Pass the salsa, let the good times roll,
Every bites a fire warmin up my soul!
From a strangers plate to a lovers smile,
Tacos bring us closer, country style!

Chorus
Its taco time, yall, grab a messy bite!
Corn and meat, so cheap, lightin up the night!
Spicy kick, hands slick, lovin every thrill,
Taco time, givin my heart a fill!

Outro
(Claps, hollers, banjo twang)
Taco time, yeah, its my new jam,
From a small-town boy to a taco man!

A jangly acoustic guitar and twangy electric riffs lead a full band with upbeat drums, a zippy fiddle, and banjo plucks, crafting a polished, radio-ready anthem. Alexs raspy vocals soar with group harmonies on the hook, backed by tambourine for a vibrant, crowd-pleasing sound.

songs.title: Friday Night Lights in Honky Tonk Heaven
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Sun sinkin' low, week's work is done
Dust off my boots, time for some fun
Got my guitar, worn and well-loved
Ready to sing 'bout the heart I've been robbed
(Chorus)
Friday night lights in Honky Tonk Heaven, yeah
Whiskey's flowin', music's playin' clear
Broken hearts mendin', laughter ringin' true
Underneath the neon glow, me and you
(Verse 2)
Saw ol' Jimmy Joe, lookin' kinda blue
Lost his woman, don't know what to do
But tonight's for forgettin', leavin' troubles behind
Let the music wash over, ease his weary mind
(Chorus)
Friday night lights in Honky Tonk Heaven, yeah
Whiskey's flowin', music's playin' clear
Broken hearts mendin', laughter ringin' true
Underneath the neon glow, me and you
(Bridge)
This ain't no church, but souls find grace here
In the twangin' guitars and the clinking of beer
We share our stories, our joys and our pain
Findin' solace 'til the sun shines again
(Chorus)
Friday night lights in Honky Tonk Heaven, yeah
Whiskey's flowin', music's playin' clear
Broken hearts mendin', laughter ringin' true
Underneath the neon glow, me and you
(Outro)
Yeah, Friday night lights, burnin' bright and bold
Another story in this Honky Tonk's been told
songs.soundsLike: This track sounds like a blend of classic Hank Williams heartbreak with the upbeat honky-tonk energy of George Jones.  The instrumentation features a driving steel guitar, a thumping stand-up bass, crisp snare drum, and a bright, twangy electric guitar providing the rhythmic backbone.  A fiddle weaves in and out, adding a touch of mournful beauty that perfectly complements the lyrics' bittersweet tone.  Willie Nelson's influence is felt in the relaxed vocal delivery, and the overall feel is reminiscent of a lively Friday night at the Tootsie Orchid Lounge, with a touch of Merle Haggard's storytelling grit.  The song concludes with a fading steel guitar and a final, lingering chord, leaving the listener with a sense of both celebration and melancholy.

songs.title: Miles of Heartache
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Sunrise paints the cotton fields, another day begins
But the light don't shine so bright no more, since you left for distant lands
Said you'd write, said you'd call, promised you'd always be near
But the miles stretched out between us, fueled by doubt and fear.
(Chorus)
Miles of heartache, winding roads of sorrow,
Every mile a memory, of a love we couldn't borrow
From the future, from the years, from a life we'd planned to share
Now just miles of heartache, and a love beyond repair.
(Verse 2)
Remember dancin' in the moonlight, beneath the summer sky?
Your laughter echoed in the fields, a song that made me fly.
We built a dream on promises, as solid as the ground
But the city lights and city life, tore our love unbound.
(Chorus)
Miles of heartache, winding roads of sorrow,
Every mile a memory, of a love we couldn't borrow
From the future, from the years, from a life we'd planned to share
Now just miles of heartache, and a love beyond repair.
(Bridge)
I keep your picture by my bed, a faded photograph
A constant reminder of the love, that distance stole, alas.
Maybe someday I'll forget, the pain that cuts so deep
But until then, these miles of heartache, are the only truth I keep.
(Chorus)
Miles of heartache, winding roads of sorrow,
Every mile a memory, of a love we couldn't borrow
From the future, from the years, from a life we'd planned to share
Now just miles of heartache, and a love beyond repair.
(Outro)
Miles miles of heartache yeah  gone
songs.soundsLike: This song sounds like a lost Hank Williams track, with a touch of George Jones's melancholic vocals and Merle Haggard's storytelling ability.  The instrumentation would be sparse but effective: a mournful steel guitar weeping throughout, a steady rhythm guitar providing a simple, heartbroken pulse, a walking bassline, and subtle fiddle flourishes in the chorus.  The drums would be restrained, keeping the focus on the vocals and the instruments' emotional delivery.  The overall feel is raw, honest, and steeped in the classic country traditions of heartbreak and longing.

songs.title: Miles of Sorrow
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Sunrise paints the cotton fields, another day begins
But the light don't shine so bright, since your love went on the winds
We built a life on promises, beneath a Georgia moon
But your city dreams called louder, than my love could ever croon
(Chorus)
Miles of sorrow stretch between us, a highway paved with tears
Each mile a memory fading, swallowed by the passing years
We said forever, honey, but forever couldn't hold
Against the pull of distance, a story left untold
(Verse 2)
Remember dancin' in the hayloft, beneath the summer stars?
Your laughter like a mockingbird, escaping rusty bars
We swore our love was stronger, than any earthly pain
But the miles kept piling higher, a relentless, driving rain
(Chorus)
Miles of sorrow stretch between us, a highway paved with tears
Each mile a memory fading, swallowed by the passing years
We said forever, honey, but forever couldn't hold
Against the pull of distance, a story left untold
(Bridge)
I see your face in every sunset, hear your voice in every breeze
But the silence in this farmhouse, just echoes my unease
I shoulda held you tighter, darling, shoulda fought with all my might
But the distance won the battle, and stole away my light
(Chorus)
Miles of sorrow stretch between us, a highway paved with tears
Each mile a memory fading, swallowed by the passing years
We said forever, honey, but forever couldn't hold
Against the pull of distance, a story left untold
(Outro)
Miles of sorrow miles and miles of sorrow
songs.soundsLike: This song sounds like a lost track from a Hank Williams, Jr. album, with a touch of George Jones' melancholic vocals. The instrumentation would feature a mournful steel guitar weeping throughout, a steady rhythm guitar providing a melancholic pulse, a walking bassline, and subtle fiddle accents during the chorus.  The overall sound is raw and emotional, focusing on the singer's heartache and the story's inherent sadness.  A simple, yet effective drum beat keeps the tempo slow and deliberate, mirroring the weight of the heartbreak.  Think classic Nashville sound with a focus on emotional delivery and traditional instrumentation.

songs.title: Soul Food
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Walked through the door, grease poppin in the air,
Cornbread steamin, loves everywhere.
Mamas in the kitchen, stirrin up a spell,
Plates piled high, where the heart can dwell.

Chorus
Soul food, oh, its lard and grace!
Fills my mind, my soul, my face!
From the skillet to the heart, its healin me whole,
Soul food, feedin body and soul!

Verse 2
Collard greens simmer, black-eyed peas sing,
Every bites a prayer, makes the spirit swing.
Round that table, laughin, stories unfold,
Warmin up the weary, worth more than gold.

Chorus
Soul food, oh, its lard and grace!
Fills my mind, my soul, my face!
From the skillet to the heart, its healin me whole,
Soul food, feedin body and soul!

Bridge
Pass the biscuits, pour the gravy high,
Feel the love that lifts you to the sky!
In this sacred spot, where the good times roll,
Lard and grace gonna save your soul!

Chorus
Soul food, oh, its lard and grace!
Fills my mind, my soul, my face!
From the skillet to the heart, its healin me whole,
Soul food, feedin body and soul!

Outro
(Claps, hollers, gospel hum)
Soul food, yeah, its where Im found,
Lard and grace, in that holy ground!
songs.soundsLike:
Acoustic Version Sound Description:

Alexs rusted guitar strums bright, open chords with a lively, gospel-infused rhythm, his gravelly vocals belting the hook with warm, infectious joy. Claps and a foot-tap pulse add raw, kitchen-jam energy, sparking singalongs.

Full Recording Version Sound Description:

A jangly acoustic guitar and soulful electric riffs lead a full band with upbeat drums, a lively piano, and gospel choir harmonies, crafting a polished, radio-ready anthem. Alexs raspy vocals soar with reverb on the hook, backed by tambourine for a vibrant, crowd-pleasing sound.

songs.title: Gimme That Black Brew
songs.lyrics:
Gimme That Black Brew

**Verse 1**  
Walked into a shop, thought Id get a cup,  
But theyre pushin green tea dust, and Im all fed up.  
Matcha this, oat milk that, five bucks for a sip,  
Tastes like lawn clippings, burns a hole in my grip.  

**Chorus**  
Gimme that black brew, punch me as it goes down!  
Strong like a mule kick, wake this small-town clown!  
No fads, no frills, just coffee dark and true,  
Gimme that black brew, thats whatll get me through!  

**Verse 2**  
Baristas talkin foam art, syrups by the score,  
I just want a jolt, not a fancy pour.  
Oat milks got no nipples, that aint no cows delight,  
Need a brew to shake me, keep me workin till the night.  

**Chorus**  
Gimme that black brew, punch me as it goes down!  
Strong like a mule kick, wake this small-town clown!  
No fads, no frills, just coffee dark and true,  
Gimme that black brew, thats whatll get me through!  

**Bridge**  
Raise a mug to the grind, to the simple and plain,  
No hipster nonsense cloggin up my brain!  
Just boil it thick, let it scald my soul,  
Black brews the fire that makes me whole!  

**Chorus**  
Gimme that black brew, punch me as it goes down!  
Strong like a mule kick, wake this small-town clown!  
No fads, no frills, just coffee dark and true,  
Gimme that black brew, thats whatll get me through!  

**Outro**  
(Claps, hollers, banjo twang)  
Gimme that black brew, none of that LA fake,  
Pour it strong, keep me wide awake!

Acoustic Version Sound Description:

Full Recording Version Sound Description:

A jangly acoustic guitar and twangy electric riffs lead a full band with lively drums, a zippy fiddle, and banjo plucks, crafting a polished, radio-ready anthem. Alexs raspy vocals soar with group harmonies on the hook, backed by tambourine for a vibrant, crowd-pleasing sound.

songs.title: That Good Old 90s Country
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
1992, dirt roads and FM gold
George Strait on the radio, stories being told
Levi's worn thin, boots kicked up high
Chattahoochee memories under Georgia sky
[Verse 2]
Garth was king and Faith was rising
Brooks & Dunn kept dance floors flying
Shania showed us what a woman feels
When country music still had steel
[Chorus]
They don't make 'em like they did back then
When three chords and truth was more than just pretend
No Auto-Tune, no drum machines
Just real songs about real dreams
That good ol' 90s country
[Bridge]
Alan Jackson taught us how to live
Travis Tritt showed what love could give
And every small-town Friday night
Was pure country done just right
[Chorus]
They don't make 'em like they did back then
When three chords and truth was more than just pretend
No Auto-Tune, no drum machines
Just real songs about real dreams
That good ol' 90s country
[Outro]
Yeah, that good ol' 90s country
When the music meant something true
That good ol' 90s country
Still running straight through my blood
That good ol' 90s country
songs.soundsLike: A traditional country ballad reminiscent of George Strait and Garth Brooks, featuring crisp steel guitar, warm fiddle, and Alex Wilson's heartfelt vocals. **Updated:** 2025-06-08

1992, dirt roads and FM gold
George Strait on the radio, stories being told
Levi's worn thin, boots kicked up high
Chattahoochee memories under Georgia sky

Garth was king and Faith was rising
Brooks & Dunn kept dance floors flying
Shania showed us what a woman feels
When country music still had steel

When three chords and truth was more than just pretend
No Auto-Tune, no drum machines
Just real songs about real dreams
That good ol' 90s country
[Bridge]
Alan Jackson taught us how to live
Travis Tritt showed what love could give
And every small-town Friday night
Was pure country done just right
[Chorus]
They don't make 'em like they did back then
When three chords and truth was more than just pretend
No Auto-Tune, no drum machines
Just real songs about real dreams
That good ol' 90s country
[Outro]
Yeah, that good ol' 90s country
When the music meant something true
That good ol' 90s country
Still running straight through my blood
That good ol' 90s country

A traditional country ballad reminiscent of George Strait and Garth Brooks, featuring crisp steel guitar, warm fiddle, and Alex Wilson's heartfelt vocals. songs.title: Country City Girl
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Left the dirt roads in the dust, for streets all shiny bright,
Swapped the quiet starry evenings for the buzz of city nights.
Packed her dreams up in a suitcase, and her mama's good advice,
Said, "I'm gonna make it out there, gonna roll them city dice!"

(Chorus)
She's got that hometown heart in the big city glow,
Learnin' new tricks, watchin' her confidence grow!
Same sweet girl, with a brand new shine,
That country-city girl, and she's all mine! (Yeah, she's all mine!)

(Verse 2)
Still knows how to bake a pie thatll make you ask for more,
Now shes charmin' all the big shots, knockin' right on fortune's door.
Takes that good ol' country common sense, gives it a big city spin,
Makes 'em wonder how a country girl just always seems to win!

(Chorus)
She's got that hometown heart in the big city glow,
Learnin' new tricks, watchin' her confidence grow!
Same sweet girl, with a brand new shine,
That country-city girl, and she's all mine! (Yeah, she's all mine!)

(Guitar/Fiddle Solo  Simple, catchy, and upbeat. Easy to hum along to.)

(Bridge)
Those city lights can't hide her smile, I see it in my mind,
She's the best of both them places, truly one of a special kind.
And Im prouder than a rooster, crowin' loud at break of day,
My country girl's a-takin' on the world, and lightin' up the way!

(Chorus)
She's got that hometown heart in the big city glow,
Learnin' new tricks, watchin' her confidence grow!
Same sweet girl, with a brand new shine,
That country-city girl, and she's all mine! (Yeah, she's all mine!)

(Outro)
In the big city glow!
Watch her go, go, go!
That country-city girl o' mine!

songs.title: Keep Singing On
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1:
Came to this town with a song in my heart,
Voice full of dreams, but the worlds played hard.
Waitin on tables, sweepin floors till dawn,
Holdin to hope when the moneys all gone.

Chorus:
Keep singin on, let the truth ring true,
Every notes a fight for the life I pursue.
Through the ache and the doubt, Ill still raise my song,
Hearts still burnin, so I keep singin on.

Verse 2:
Mamas voice echoes, said Id shine someday,
But shes gone to glory, and Im still findin my way.
This old guitars my only friend some nights,
Singin to shadows, chasin stage lights.

Chorus:
Keep singin on, let the truth ring true,
Every notes a fight for the life I pursue.
Through the ache and the doubt, Ill still raise my song,
Hearts still burnin, so I keep singin on.

Bridge:
Bills stack high, and the dreams wear thin,
But my souls got a fire that wont give in.
Every scars a story, every tears a call,
Ill sing through the silence till Ive given it all.

Chorus:
Keep singin on, let the truth ring true,
Every notes a fight for the life I pursue.
Through the ache and the doubt, Ill still raise my song,
Hearts still burnin, so I keep singin on.

Outro:
So heres my voice, let it carry me home,
Through empty rooms where my dreams still roam.
No matter how heavy, Ill carry this dawn,
With love in my heart, I keep singin on.
songs.soundsLike: Clean acoustic guitar establishes an inviting groove, paired with gentle kick drum, upright bass for warmth, and subtle fiddle fills, Rich, soulful female country soul vocals rise with natural reverb; harmonies and mandolin brighten the choruses, The arrangement remains polished yet rootsy

songs.title: Roots Torn Slow
songs.lyrics:
Some folks leave like a gust through the pines,
Fast and loud, gone before the nights decline.
But you left like roots ripped from the ground,
Slow and breakin, didnt make a sound.
I stood there watchin, my heart in my hands,
Pieces of me scattered cross this lonesome land.
(Pre-Chorus)
Every step feels like Im circlin a scar,
A hollow where you were, where you tore me apart.
(Chorus)
Roots torn slow, they dont just fade away,
They leave a hole that haunts me every day.
I walk like Im growin round the pain,
Plantin flowers in the dirt where you remained.
They bloom deeper, they know what Ive lost,
They choose sunlight, no matter the cost.
(Verse 2)
I used to think love was a fire that burned,
But yours was a weight, a lesson I learned.
Each crack in my soul, it taught me to fight,
To find my own spark in the cold, endless night.
Now Im sowin seeds where the shadows still creep,
Buildin a garden from the hurt runnin deep.
(Pre-Chorus)
Every blooms a battle, every petals a prayer,
Proof Im still standin, though you aint there.
(Chorus)
Roots torn slow, they dont just fade away,
They leave a hole that haunts me every day.
I walk like Im growin round the pain,
Plantin flowers in the dirt where you remained.
They bloom deeper, they know what Ive lost,
They choose sunlight, no matter the cost.
(Bridge)
I aint the girl you left in the dust,
My hearts got thorns now, forged from the rust.
But these hands still dig, they still reach for the sky,
Turnin tears into roses that wont ever die.
Your leavin broke me, but it made me whole,
I found my roots in this stubborn soul.
(Chorus)
Roots torn slow, they dont just fade away,
They leave a hole that haunts me every day.
I walk like Im growin round the pain,
Plantin flowers in the dirt where you remained.
They bloom deeper, they know what Ive lost,
They choose sunlight, no matter the cost.
(Outro)
Some leave like wind, but you left like stone,
Tore out my roots, but Im growin my own.
These flowers I plant, theyre my hearts quiet vow,
They bloom deeper and Im stronger now.
songs.soundsLike: The song is a mid-tempo country lament, blending traditional and modern elements, designed for a female vocalist with a powerful, emotive range

songs.title: The Road to Nashville
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Got a beat-up truck and a guitar case,
Dreams burnin hotter than a summers blaze.
Leavin small-town dust in my rearview glow,
Headed where the neon lights call my soul.

Chorus
On the road to Nashville, sing it loud and free!
Chasin stars and honky-tonks, where Im meant to be!
From the backroads to the bright lights, feel the thrill,
On the road to Nashville, Im climbin that hill!

Verse 2
Sweet tea sippin, boots tappin the floor,
Singin my heart out, knockin on doors.
Every miles a story, every notes a fight,
Southern grits pushin me through the night.

Chorus
On the road to Nashville, sing it loud and free!
Chasin stars and honky-tonks, where Im meant to be!
From the backroads to the bright lights, feel the thrill,
On the road to Nashville, Im climbin that hill!

Bridge
Raise a bottle, let the fiddle wail,
Every dreamers got a tale to tell!
With a song in my soul and fire in my veins,
Nashvilles callin, breakin all my chains!

Chorus
On the road to Nashville, sing it loud and free!
Chasin stars and honky-tonks, where Im meant to be!
From the backroads to the bright lights, feel the thrill,
On the road to Nashville, Im climbin that hill!

Outro
(Claps, hollers, banjo rolls)
On the road to Nashville, never standin still,
Sing it proud, keep pushin, got a dream to fill!
From the heartland to the stage, Im risin high,
On the road to Nashville, reachin for the sky!
songs.soundsLike: Bright, jangly acoustic and twangy electric guitar riffs kick off this anthem, joined by driving drums, lively fiddle, and crisp banjo plucks, Alexs raspy vocals ride atop, with bold group harmonies on the infectious hook, Tambourine and organ round out the arrangement, adding energy and warmth

songs.title: Coal Dust on the Lamb
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Sixteen summers bleedin' into fall,
Daddy's shadow stretched across the wall.
His words like whiskey, burnin' down my throat,
Kicked me out to wander, wearin' a thin coat.
Pikeville hollers echoed with my shame,
Innocence a flicker, dyin' in the flame.

(Verse 2)
Found a floor to sleep on, kindness in a stranger's eye,
But the mountain cold seeped in, beneath a starless sky.
Traded school books for a pick and shovel's weight,
Coal dust settled on my dreams, sealin' up their fate.
This broken arm, a constant ache, a twisted memory,
Of a boy who used to dream beneath a dogwood tree.

(Chorus)
Coal dust on the lamb, a stain that won't come clean,
Lost my way back home, a forgotten, faded scene.
These coal-stained hands, they hold the weight of sin,
Prayin' for redemption, hopin' God lets me in.

(Verse 3)
Sunrise paints the mountain ridge, a fiery, bloody hue,
Another day of breakin' back, another debt to accrue.
The fields stretch out before me, endless rows of green,
But all I see is darkness, a fractured, broken scene.
This ain't the life I pictured,  beneath the mountain's gaze,
Just a broken boy, lost in a lonely, hazy maze.

(Bridge)
Mama's hymnals echo, a whisper in the wind,
A memory of comfort, a peace I can't pretend.
Will I ever feel that grace again, that gentle, lovin' hand?
Or am I destined to wander, a ghost in this promised land?

(Chorus)
Coal dust on the lamb, a stain that won't come clean,
Lost my way back home, a forgotten, faded scene.
These coal-stained hands, they hold the weight of sin,
Prayin' for redemption, hopin' God lets me in.

(Outro)
Lord, have mercy, on this coal-stained soul,
Lead me back to the fold, make me whole. 
Make me whole.
songs.soundsLike: Opening with fingerpicked acoustic guitar and sparse banjo, the song weaves in subtle brushed drums, Layered harmonies build a haunting folk-rock atmosphere, while occasional pedal steel and gentle bass deepen the soundscape, The arrangement remains spacious, evoking lingering tension

songs.title: Empty Seat
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1

Every mornin shed slip through that diner door,

Same old booth, coffee black, nothin more.

Never spoke, just stared where the shadows creep,

Today her seats empty, and the silence cuts deep.

Chorus

Oh, the empty seat, whered she go?

Carried her story where nobody knows.

A ghost in the booth, left a chill in the air,

Empty seats whisperin, she aint there.

Verse 2

Worn-out coat, eyes like a lonesome rain,

No one asked her story, not even her name.

Waitress hums soft, but the counter feels wrong,

Her shadows gone quiet, where it used to belong.

Chorus

Oh, the empty seat, whered she go?

Carried her story where nobody knows.

A ghost in the booth, left a chill in the air,

Empty seats whisperin, she aint there.

Bridge

Was she runnin from hurt, or chasin a dream?

Lost in the cracks of a lifes frayed seam.

That booth holds her echo, a truth left unsaid,

A strangers gone missin, but she aint dead.

Chorus

Oh, the empty seat, whered she go?

Carried her story where nobody knows.

A ghost in the booth, left a chill in the air,

Empty seats whisperin, she aint there.

Outro

In that small-town diner, neath the hum of the light,

Her seat stays empty, through the long, lonesome night.
songs.soundsLike: Delicate acoustic guitar fingerpicking opens alongside soft bass and brushed drums, creating a warm underpinning, Mournful pedal steel weaves in for haunting texture, Alexs raspy, reverberant vocals lead, subtly layered by harmonies in the chorus, crafting a polished country-blues mood

songs.title: The Songs That Saved Me
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
In a trailers shadow, where the silence screamed,
Found a rusted guitar, chased a broken dream.
Johnnys voice of hurt cut through my pain,
Waylons rebel soul kept me sane.

Chorus
Songs that saved me, pullin me through,
Truth in the darkness, love thats true.
From the graves cold call to a hearts soft plea,
These old songs, theyre savin me.

Verse 2
Stapletons gravel wrapped my scars in grace,
Childers sang the hills where I found my place.
Adeles fire burned my doubts away,
Each note a light in my lonesome day.

Chorus
Songs that saved me, pullin me through,
Truth in the darkness, love thats true.
From the graves cold call to a hearts soft plea,
These old songs, theyre savin me.

Bridge
Hurt taught me wounds can sing out loud,
Cover Me Up showed loves the proudest sound.
O Death whispered lifes a fleeting flame,
Their truths carved my heart, gave me my name.

Chorus
Songs that saved me, pullin me through,
Truth in the darkness, love thats true.
From the graves cold call to a hearts soft plea,
These old songs, theyre savin me.

Outro
Now I strum my truth neath a lonesome sky,
Carryin their echoes till the day I die.
Through the pain and love, their voices I see,
These old songs, forever savin me.
songs.soundsLike: Jangly acoustic guitar sets the upbeat pace, joined by twangy electric riffs and thumping drums, Banjo and lively fiddle interweave through verses and choruses, while tambourine and organ add energy, Alexs raspy vocals soar atop rich group harmonies, creating a polished, radio-ready anthem

Truth in the darkness, love thats true.
From the graves cold call to a hearts soft plea,
These old songs, theyre savin me.

Outro
Now I strum my truth neath a lonesome sky,
Carryin their echoes till the day I die.
Through the pain and love, their voices I see,
These old songs, forever savin me.

### Sounds Like
Jangly acoustic guitar sets the upbeat pace, joined by twangy electric riffs and thumping drums, Banjo and lively fiddle interweave through verses and choruses, while tambourine and organ add energy, Alexs raspy vocals soar atop rich group harmonies, creating a polished, radio-ready anthem

Singin bout Georgia and the Devils dance,
Just a bluff-top dreamer takin one wild chance!

Crowd packed tight at the towns old bar,
Hollered Id get nekked, pushed it just too far.

songs.title: Keep Singin On
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1:
Came to this town with a song in my heart,
Voice full of dreams, but the worlds played hard.
Waitin on tables, sweepin floors till dawn,
Holdin to hope when the moneys all gone.
Chorus:
Keep singin on, let the truth ring true,
Every notes a fight for the life I pursue.
Through the ache and the doubt, Ill still raise my song,
Hearts still burnin, so I keep singin on.
Verse 2:
Mamas voice echoes, said Id shine someday,
But shes gone to glory, and Im still findin my way.
This old guitars my only friend some nights,
Singin to shadows, chasin stage lights.
Chorus:
Keep singin on, let the truth ring true,
Every notes a fight for the life I pursue.
Through the ache and the doubt, Ill still raise my song,
Hearts still burnin, so I keep singin on.
Bridge:
Bills stack high, and the dreams wear thin,
But my souls got a fire that wont give in.
Every scars a story, every tears a call,
Ill sing through the silence till Ive given it all.
Chorus:
Keep singin on, let the truth ring true,
Every notes a fight for the life I pursue.
Through the ache and the doubt, Ill still raise my song,
Hearts still burnin, so I keep singin on.
Outro:
So heres my voice, let it carry me home,
Through empty rooms where my dreams still roam.
No matter how heavy, Ill carry this dawn,
With love in my heart, I keep singin on.
songs.soundsLike:
Acoustic: Alex plays on his rusted guitar, the slightly sharp strings ringing with open chords (G, C, D, Am). His gravelly vocals carry a warm, steady cadence, rising in the chorus with a hopeful lift, the songs intimacy suiting a garage jam for Maria.
Full Studio: A clean acoustic guitar leads, backed by a gentle kick drum, upright bass, and subtle fiddle fills. Marias vocals (imagined as rich and soulful) soar with reverb, harmonies in the chorus, and a mandolin adding sparkle, creating a polished yet rootsy country track.

songs.title: Forever Happy
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1:
Stepped to the edge where the blue runs free,
Waves hit my heart like a melody.
Suns shinin down, got a brand-new view,
Every moments brighter cause Im here with you.
Chorus:
Watchin forever and comin away happy,
Souls on fire, and my hearts snappin snappy.
Oceans singin, and Im feelin alive,
Watchin forever, gonna thrive, gonna thrive!
Verse 2:
Kick off my boots, let the sand take hold,
Your smiles the spark thats worth more than gold.
Laughin in the breeze, were a carefree song,
Dancin with the waves, where we both belong.
Chorus:
Watchin forever and comin away happy,
Souls on fire, and my hearts snappin snappy.
Oceans singin, and Im feelin alive,
Watchin forever, gonna thrive, gonna thrive!
Bridge:
Aint no worries when the tide rolls in,
Every heartbeats where our story begins.
Raise a glass to the sky, let the good times soar,
This kinda joys what were livin for.
Chorus:
Watchin forever and comin away happy,
Souls on fire, and my hearts snappin snappy.
Oceans singin, and Im feelin alive,
Watchin forever, gonna thrive, gonna thrive!
Outro:
Yeah, watchin forever with a grin ear to ear,
Got this moment, and Im holdin it near.
Comin away happy, gonna shout to the sky,
Watchin forever, well never say goodbye!
songs.soundsLike:
Acoustic Version Sound Description:
Alexs rusted guitar strums bright, major chords with a lively, wave-like rhythm, its gritty tone blending with his gravelly, joyful vocals. The performance is raw and intimate, with a faint string buzz and ocean waves adding a sunny, beachside charm.
Full Studio Version Sound Description:
A crisp acoustic guitar leads a full band with driving drums, twangy electric riffs, and a bouncy fiddle, creating a vibrant, radio-ready anthem. Alexs raspy vocals soar with reverb and harmonies, backed by banjo and tambourine for a polished, summery feel.

songs.title: Through the Silence
songs.description:
Acoustic Version Sound Description:
Setting: Imagine Alex sitting on the tailgate of his truck, parked on a bluff overlooking LA at dusk, his rusted guitar in hand, playing for Shay or just the wind, as he often does. The performance is raw, unamplified, and deeply personal, reflecting his self-taught, solitary style.
Sound:
  Guitar: The rusted guitar, with its slightly out-of-tune strings, produces a gritty, resonant tone. Alex uses open chords (G, C, D, Am) with a slow, deliberate strumming pattern, letting each note ring out. The verse has a sparse, fingerpicked intro, transitioning to a fuller strum in the chorus for emotional weight. The bridge softens to a near-whisper, with single-string plucks emphasizing vulnerability.
  Vocals: Alexs voice is gravelly and unpolished, like Chris Stapleton after a long night, carrying the weight of his Pikeville scars. He sings low and measured in the verses, letting the lyrics pain breathe. The chorus builds with a raw intensity, his voice cracking slightly on sing the truth, conveying survival. The outro fades with a softer, almost spoken delivery, like a prayer.
  Arrangement: No backing instrumentsjust Alex and his guitar. The tempo is moderate (around 80 BPM), with natural pauses after silence in the chorus, mimicking the quiet he sings about. The songs dynamic shifts come from his voice and strumming intensity, peaking in the bridge and easing in the outro.
  Atmosphere: The performance feels intimate, like a confession. The guitars imperfections (a faint buzz on the low E string) and Alexs unrefined vocals mirror his lifes roughness. Background soundscrickets, a distant LA humblend into the song, grounding it in the moment. Its the kind of performance that makes Shays eyes well up, hearing his truth laid bare.
Vibe: Think Johnny Cashs Hurt (acoustic cover) meets Tyler Childers Feathered Indiansraw, haunting, and deeply felt, with no need for polish. Its Alex at his core, singing to process his past, not to perform.

songs.title: Going Viral
songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Started with some coffee, or what they call it here,
Talkin' 'bout oat nipples, made Shay Bear grin ear to ear.
Then a goat in a sweater, name of Harold, if you please,
Had me on the pavement, laughin' till I couldn't breathe.
Moonbeam had a guitar, hangin' like a piece of art,
Said it needed playin', right from my Kentucky heart.
(Chorus)
Now they say I'm goin' viral, whatever that might mean,
Little screens all lit up, the craziest damn thing I've seen.
Singin' 'bout sad porridge and Harold in his Sunday best,
Just a red dirt drifter puttin' feelings to the test,
Out here in this LA sun, ain't like no place I know,
Wonderin' how a whisper turned into a picture show.
(Verse 2)
Jumped up on a table, sang about this crazy town,
The words just came on out, as the folks all gathered 'round.
Then I sang 'bout hardship, and that guitar from the trash,
Felt the whole world listen, saw the tears begin to splash.
Shay was lookin' prouder than I'd ever seen her look,
Like she knew these city folks would read me like a book.
(Chorus)
Now they say I'm goin' viral, whatever that might mean,
Little screens all lit up, the craziest damn thing I've seen.
Singin' 'bout sad porridge and Harold in his Sunday best,
Just a red dirt drifter puttin' feelings to the test,
Out here in this LA sun, ain't like no place I know,
Wonderin' how a whisper turned into a picture show.
(Bridge)
Ain't never chased no spotlight, ain't my kind of game,
Just sing my truth out quiet, whisper Shay Bear's name.
But if my rusty-string stories, 'bout the hurt and hope I've known,
Can make a stranger out there feel a little less alone...
Well, maybe there's a reason this wild seed was sown.
(Chorus)
Now they say I'm goin' viral, whatever that might mean,
Little screens all lit up, the craziest damn thing I've seen.
Singin' 'bout sad porridge and Harold in his Sunday best,
Just a red dirt drifter puttin' feelings to the test,
Out here in this LA sun, ain't like no place I know,
Wonderin' how a whisper turned into a picture show.
(Outro)
Yeah, a picture show... full of folks I've never met.
Still don't get this "viral," ain't quite figured it out yet.
Just got my girl, my guitar... and I guess Harold the goat.
(Guitar fades out with a soft, questioning strum)
songs.soundsLike: Simple, honest acoustic guitar intro  maybe a few thoughtful, slightly questioning chords

songs.lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Sunrise paints these Blue Ridge Mountains, but I'm already caked in mine grime
Another shift done, countin' pennies, losin' track of time.
This old pickup's my four walls now, under the Kentucky moon so wide
But thinkin' of your West Coast smile, girl, eases the ache inside.
(Chorus)
Hey, Shay, my Kentucky Heartbeat, my steady ground so true,
Miles can't change this rhythm I only find in you.
Every sunrise I fight for, every dollar I make,
Is for your California dream, no matter what it takes.
(Verse 2)
Remember Blackberry Creek, dust devils dancin' in the summer heat?
Felt like magic then, your hand in mine, oh, bitter and so sweet.
Now your picture on the dash, it guides me through the dark and lonely road
Helps me carry every burden, helps me lift this heavy load.
(Chorus)
Hey, Shay, my Kentucky Heartbeat, my steady ground so true,
Miles can't change this rhythm I only find in you.
Every sunrise I fight for, every dollar I make,
Is for your California dream, no matter what it takes.
(Bridge)
These calloused hands have known the sting of cold and burnin' steel
Played a rusted, found guitar, makin' all this heartache real.
But you heard the truth within the noise, a song beneath the pain
My Shay Bear, your belief in me, it washes off the stains.
(Chorus)
Hey, Shay, my Kentucky Heartbeat, my steady ground so true,
Miles can't change this rhythm I only find in you.
Every sunrise I fight for, every dollar I make,
Is for your California dream, no matter what it takes.
(Outro)
Yeah, my Kentucky Heartbeat, thumpin' just for you, Shay Bear.
More than just some words, girl, this is my earnest prayer.
My truth, my song, for you
songs.soundsLike:

A surprisingly intricate blend of a hard-running, percussive rhythm from a notably resonant, time-worn acoustic guitar and elegant, self-taught fingerpicking underpins a raw, deep, and gravelly lead vocal that commands attention.
Full Recording Sounds Like:
A powerful, deep, and gravelly lead vocal soars above intricate, riff-driven acoustic guitar and sophisticated fingerpicking, all propelled by a tight, driving rhythm section and richly layered with mournful or fiery fiddle lines, weeping steel guitar, and warm, soulful keyboard textures, creating an authentic synthesis of classic outlaw country and modern Americana.

songs.title: Devil Came Back for Georgia
songs.lyrics:
The Devil Came Back to Georgia
The Devil came back to Georgia,
He was burnin for a second round.
That first defeat left his pride in heat,
And he craved that sultry sound.
He found her swayin by a riverside,
Under stars that pulsed with sin,
Her eyes like coals, she stirred his soul,
And he swore hed win her grin.
Well, darlin, Im back, he purred with a leer,
Got a new game to ignite.
You scorched me once, but Im no dunce,
This time Ill own the night.
He flicked his tongue, let the shadows hum,
And the air grew thick with lust.
Ill raise the stakes, make no mistake,
This dancell turn you to dust.
Georgia laughed, her voice like wine,
Devil, youre barkin up my tree.
You think youre sly, but Ill make you cry,
Cause this fire belongs to me.
She stepped in close, her breath a tease,
Let her fingers graze his chest.
Bring your best, Ill do the rest,
And put your wicked heart to rest.
Chorus:
Sparks on the river, flames in the dark,
Georgias got that untamed spark.
Velvet and venom, a dangerous game,
The Devils lost in Georgias flame.
The Devil moved with a serpents grace,
Every touch a fevered spell.
He wove his charm, thought hed do no harm,
But Georgia knew his hell.
She matched his heat, step for step,
Her hips a taunting dare,
Each whispered word made his senses blur,
Till he was drowning in her stare.
When the dawn crept soft through the cypress shade,
The Devil knelt, undone.
Georgia smirked, her magic worked,
Shed played him til shed won.
You thought youd tame me, sweet Lucifer,
But Im the queen of this domain.
She blew a kiss, left him in bliss,
And sent him back to his pain.
Chorus:
Sparks on the river, flames in the dark,
Georgias got that untamed spark.
Velvet and venom, a dangerous game,
The Devils lost in Georgias flame.
Outro:
The Devil came back to Georgia,
But Georgia stole the crown.
She spun that sly ol sinner
And burned his kingdom down.

songs.title: Drivin to You
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Kicked off from Kentucky, tires spinnin through the night,
Your dreams in California, girl, Im racin toward your light.
Tennessees hills are callin, with their banjo serenade,
Arkansas muddy deltas where your memorys never strayed.
Pre-Chorus
Radios buzzin, but your voice is my guide,
Every states a promise, Im crossin the divide.
Chorus
From Texas to California, Im ridin into LA!
Drivin to you, darlin, no states too far away!
Oklahoma to Nevada, Im burnin up the miles,
Sing it loud, Im comin for your heart and your smile!
Your dreams my compass, Im chasin your glow,
From Texas to California, girl, here I go!
Verse 2
Oklahomas plains are screamin, wind tearin at my soul,
Texas stars light the way, your face in their fiery roll.
Missouris rivers churn wild, reflectin your sweet spark,
New Mexicos desert heat cant stop this racin heart.
Pre-Chorus
Coffees cold as stone, but my hearts runnin hot,
This highways my heartstring, tyin all I got.
Chorus
From Texas to California, Im ridin into LA!
Drivin to you, darlin, no states too far away!
Oklahoma to Nevada, Im burnin up the miles,
Sing it loud, Im comin for your heart and your smile!
Your dreams my compass, Im chasin your glow,
From Texas to California, girl, here I go!
Bridge
Colorados peaks stand tall, Arizonas canyons wail,
Nevadas neon flickers, but your loves my holy grail.
Id blaze through every state line, fight the wind and the storm,
For one night in your arms, keepin my heart warm.
Chorus
From Texas to California, Im ridin into LA!
Drivin to you, darlin, no states too far away!
Oklahoma to Nevada, Im burnin up the miles,
Sing it loud, Im comin for your heart and your smile!
Your dreams my compass, Im chasin your glow,
From Texas to California, girl, here I go!
Outro
From Texas to California, sunrise breakin through,
This roads my love, and its leadin to you.
songs.soundsLike:
Sounds Like Acoustic: A high-energy, road-charged acoustic banger with Alex Wilsons Appalachian fire, featuring a relentless acoustic guitar strum, a wild fiddle that roars like a revving engine, and a steel guitar humming like a highways pulse, evoking the heart-pounding rush of a cross-country love chase.
Sounds Like Recording: A thumping pop-country anthem with a turbo-charged beat, layered electric and acoustic guitars, a booming bassline, and Alexs gravelly vocals belting a chant-ready hook, built to dominate Billboards Hot Country Songs with Blake Sheltons bold swagger, perfect for highway cruises or arena-shaking sing-alongs.

songs.title: Coal Dust Sunrise
songs.lyrics:
Long shadows creep on the valley floor,
As the bleeding sky unveils what's in store.
A cold breath sighs through the hollows deep,
Where old dreams stir and new promises keep.
A shack stands weathered, a whisper of gray,
But a tender warmth chases shadows away.
A soft hymn rises on the morning's chill,
A silent plea, standing perfectly still.
(Pre-Chorus)
Beneath the grit, a spark ignites,
Chasing the ghosts of endless nights.
This ain't no Eden, raw and deep,
But promises the weary keep.
(Chorus)
These coal dust sunrises, they stain the peaks in gray,
But hope's true fire still finds a way, yeah, it always finds a way.
The tired earth groans, a haunting, low refrain,
Yet grit-worn hands find strength to rise and live again.
To rise and breathe again.
(Verse 2)
The earth gives freely, then demands its toll,
Each dawn a testament to body and soul.
Redemption's whisper in the morning's light,
A bruising struggle, a constant, inner fight.
A flicker of grace, a beacon in the night,
A stubborn promise burning ever so bright.
The scars remain, a map of every pain,
But the spirit's song, a fierce, unbroken strain.
(Pre-Chorus)
Beneath the grit, a spark ignites,
Chasing the ghosts of endless nights.
This ain't no Eden, raw and deep,
But promises the weary keep.
(Chorus)
These coal dust sunrises, they stain the peaks in gray,
But hope's true fire still finds a way, yeah, it always finds a way.
The tired earth groans, a haunting, low refrain,
Yet grit-worn hands find strength to rise and live again.
To rise and breathe again.
(Bridge)
The mountain stands, a titan through the years,
Swallowing hardship, conquering all fears.
This ain't the ending, just a beat in between,
A chance to reclaim, to heal, to be seen.
(Chorus)
These coal dust sunrises, they stain the peaks in gray,
But hope's true fire still finds a way, yeah, it always finds a way.
The tired earth groans, a haunting, low refrain,
Yet grit-worn hands find strength to rise and live again.
To rise and breathe again.
(Outro)
To rise and breathe again,
A coal dust sunrise, and we're all risin' again.

Sounds like Recording: A blend of acoustic and electric instruments, featuring slide guitar, banjo, and subtle drums, create a rootsy, Americana sound with a driving, anthemic chorus.

songs.title: Wild LA
songs.lyrics:
Verse 1
Im a red dirt drifter, boots scarred from the clay,
Dropped in this jungle they call LA.
Oat milk in my coffee? That aint milk, I reckon,
Oats dont got nipples, yall messin with my head, son.
Pre-Chorus
Kombucha flights and candles with a prayer,
Farmers markets a circus, patchouli in the air.
Chorus
Wild LA, where the kales got a soul,
Im a fish outta water, but Im keepin my roll.
From raw almond jerky to goats in a sweater,
Im laughin through the madness, this hearts gettin better.
Grounded in the holler, but Im ridin this wave,
Singin my truth in the heart of Wild LA!
Verse 2
Celery smoothies run eleven bucks a pop,
Mushrooms get a massage fore they hit the shop.
Man buns pluckin banjo, bought it off the net,
But them bruised-up apples? Thats the realest Ive met.
Pre-Chorus
Charcoal lavender brew, moonlight in a glass,
Im dodgin astral vibes, holdin onto my sass.
Chorus
Wild LA, where the kales got a soul,
Im a fish outta water, but Im keepin my roll.
From raw almond jerky to goats in a sweater,
Im laughin through the madness, this hearts gettin better.
Grounded in the holler, but Im ridin this wave,
Singin my truth in the heart of Wild LA!
Bridge
Met a goat named Harold, sportin knitwear fine,
Chewin like a sage, got me losin my mind.
Shays wheezin laughter, says Im too much sense,
But this crazy towns sparks breakin down my defense.
Chorus
Wild LA, where the kales got a soul,
Im a fish outta water, but Im keepin my roll.
From raw almond jerky to goats in a sweater,
Im laughin through the madness, this hearts gettin better.
Grounded in the holler, but Im ridin this wave,
Singin my truth in the heart of Wild LA!
Outro
(Fiddle rips, upbeat strum)
Wild LA, with Harolds sweater in view,
This red dirt boys found a home in the zoo.
songs.soundsLike:
Sounds like Acoustic: Upbeat, folksy country with a driving acoustic guitar rhythm, banjo plucking, and a prominent fiddle adding a playful, down-home feel.
Sounds like Recording:  A polished country-pop production with bright electric guitars, crisp drums, layered banjo and fiddle, and a touch of steel guitar adding a nostalgic warmth.
